Member of literature & cultural development group/Arts and Humanity group

I take pride in giving advice to fellow students. I run a cultural group which brings together 100 Youth of uMhlathuze municipality, South Africa, I try to bring the people together throught cultural activities i organize and liberate their minds via discussion & writing poetry. I hosted Profile Volunteers of Rotary with Assuring Youth Abroad (AYA) San Diego (USA). I participated in RHUF, Tanzania.

Professionally: I work as a Disability Advisor at Umlalazi Youth Center Assisting Youth with Disabilities on Employability. https://www.linkedin.com/in/sohail-baig-d1088117/ I Consider myself more of a student, than a worker of disability issues. I state: “More than fifty years have ensued since the International Labour Organization (ILO) adopted what has come to be known as the Rights of the Disabled Persons Convention which was adopted in 1975.

This Convention stated at that time that to the extent that any of its provisions are not directly applicable at the date of entry into force of the present Convention, these provisions shall be considered as the minimum standard.

I am blessed to be trained as Disability Resource Person by NIZA Holland, and IDDT-International Physiother
